  <section class="page-section" aria-labelledby="section-new-here">
    <h2 class="section-heading" id="section-new-here">Never Done This Before?</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">Most people who come to a jam have never been on a stage. That is the point. Here is the order we would walk a friend through it.</p>

    <ol class="about-ladder">
      <li>
        <span class="about-ladder-step">1</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Come to a Whimsical Wednesday</strong>
          <p>Our jam. Leave your inhibitions at the door, play a few games, see what improv actually feels like. No experience, no pressure.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="about-ladder-step">2</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Make friends with the stage</strong>
          <p>When you want to do more than watch, this is the open-stage jam built for it. Short scenes, we keep things moving, you step in and out as you like.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="about-ladder-step">3</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Take Improv 101</strong>
          <p>A proper first workshop, built around how not to panic on stage. By the end you are doing scenes and enjoying it.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="about-ladder-step">4</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Find your thing</strong>
          <p>Musical improv, our longer courses, and the formats that make up our shows. Go as deep as you want.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>

